    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PC's Under Surveillance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jim Detmer letter says using spy software (June 22 article) is like using a wiretap</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I think that the use of spy software is like using a wiretap, and I think that that the same legal requirements should be imposed (''Spy Software Puts Home PC's Under Surveillance,'' State of the Art, June 22). I am sure that countermeasures will appear very quickly in the marketplace. Who will use the hotel or cybercafe system until this is all sorted out? Not me!</p>
        <p>JIM DETMER  Williamsburg, Va.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
